---
By: Cicero
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 337
    Verse: 9
Tags:
  - Senility is not confined to old
---
Each part of life has its own pleasures. Each has its own abundant harvest,
to be garnered in season. We may grow old in body, but we need never grow
old in mind and spirit. ... No one is as old as to think he cannot live one
more year.
